{
  "stem": "26765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I strike up a very nice friendship with two girls with whom I'm still very close friends with.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then in April 14 of 1947, I said goodbye to Rector Wijers and to the nuns and to my friends there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was very hard, very difficult for us, again, separation, and I came here to my aunt and uncle in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "M-hm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my aunt and uncle were well-meaning people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncle was Catholic, a Catholic physician who had left Germany already in 1933 and had told my father to leave Germany, but my father could not believe that anything could happen to him or his family.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so he did not leave.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my uncle had already left in '33.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But on the way from the airport, my aunt said to my brother and me, we would like you to take on the name of Mueller instead of Levy.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Levy is a Jewish name, and you will have an easier time with a name like Mueller.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, that didn't quite sound right to me, but George didn't say anything, my brother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't say anything either.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I felt like I was losing what little identity I still had, what few ties I still had with my parents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Of course, I still was very Catholic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My aunt and uncle sent me to a Catholic school, which I was very happy with because I was familiar with the nuns, and again, I struck up a friendship with one of my teachers, a nun.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when I was about 16, 17, I started to have my doubts.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
